# Golden Set Evals

## Required Structure

Every case MUST have all 6 fields. Never omit any.

```yaml
- id: "gs-tool-001"
  query: "user question here"
  expected_tools:
    - getPortfolioSnapshot
  expected_sources:
    - getPortfolioSnapshot
  must_contain:
    - "key fact"
    - "another fact"
  must_not_contain:
    - "I don't know"
    - "no information"
```

## 4 Checks — All Required Per Tool

1. **Tool selection** — assert the right tool was called
2. **Source citation** — assert the right source was cited
3. **Content validation** — assert key facts appear in the response
4. **Negative validation** — assert no hallucination markers appear

## Size Rules

- 10–20 cases per tool (at least 2–3 minimum)
- At least 1 ambiguous case per tool (non-obvious tool choice)
- At least 1 edge case per tool (empty result or out-of-scope query)
- Full suite must run in under 5 minutes
- Run on every commit — treat like unit tests

## Evaluator Script Rules (run-evals.ts)

When writing or modifying `run-evals.ts`:

- Exit code 1 if ANY case fails
- Support `--verbose` and `--id` flags
- Print case ID + failed assertion + actual output for every failure
- Print final summary: X/Y passed (Z%)
- Never catch and swallow assertion errors silently

## Never Do These

- Change expected output to make a failing test pass
- Use vague checks ("response is helpful", "answer looks good")
- Use token count as a quality signal
- Skip the `must_not_contain` field
- Use LLM-as-judge inside golden set checks — binary only
- **ALWAYS** add a new golden case when a production bug is found

## File Layout (this project)

```
src/server/evals/
  golden_sets/
    {tool_name}.eval.yaml
  sanity_sets/
    sanity.eval.yaml     ← 1–2 cases per tool; use during TDD to save API credits
  scenario_sets/
    edge_cases.eval.yaml
    adversarial.eval.yaml
    multi_step.eval.yaml
  run-evals.ts
```

**Run commands:** `npm run evals:sanity` | `npm run evals:golden` | `npm run evals:scenarios` | `npm run evals:all`

**Re-run only failed:** After a run with failures, re-run just the failed evals with `npm run evals:sanity -- --retry-failed` (or the set you used). Failed IDs are logged and saved; keep using `--retry-failed` until all pass.

**TDD / Cursor / Claude:** When doing TDD or iterating with Cursor/Claude, run **only the sanity set** (`npm run evals:sanity`). After failures, use `--retry-failed` to re-run only failed evals. Use the full golden set before commit or in CI.
